; preludes: form-stdlib/core.fk form-stdlib/slice-merge.fk form-stdlib/mesh-merge-converge.fk
;
; mesh-merge-converge-band — gossip convergence as a value proof: the same deltas merge to ONE value
; no matter which path the mesh delivers them by (federated-slices.form M2, three-way).
;
; Three cells offer deltas for the same base slice:
;   A = weight 2, delta [ 3  -2   5]
;   B = weight 1, delta [ 1   4  -5]
;   C = weight 3, delta [ 2  -1  -4]
; Coordinate by coordinate (slice-merge's TIES sign-election + trust-weighted FedAvg):
;   j=0: all "+"            -> elect +;  num = 2·3 + 1·1 + 3·2 = 13,  den = 2+1+3 = 6
;   j=1: A:-2(w2) B:+4(w1) C:-1(w3) -> "−" wins (5 ≥ 1) -> elect −;  num = 2·(−2) + 3·(−1) = −7, den = 2+3 = 5
;   j=2: A:+5(w2) B:-5(w1) C:-4(w3) -> "−" wins (4 ≥ 2) -> elect −;  num = 1·(−5) + 3·(−4) = −17, den = 1+3 = 4
; The merge is a fold of integer add over the slice list, so it is commutative AND associative — the
; merged value is identical across ALL SIX orderings of {A,B,C} (A→B→C, C→B→A, and the four others), and
; a weight-0 gone peer joins without moving it. That is gossip convergence: mesh-merge == local-merge.
;
; Verdict 127 when every claim lands:
;   1   the merge computes the right numerator   (mm-num coord0 == 13)
;   2   the merge computes the right denominator (mm-den coord0 == 6)
;   4   a→b→c converges with c→b→a (full reverse, the named diagonal — 3 coords agree)
;   8   order-stable across ALL SIX permutations of {A,B,C}  (the core gossip-convergence claim)
;   16  sign-election survives reordering         (mm-num coord2 == −17, the elected − side, not all-+)
;   32  a gone peer (weight 0) does not move the merge  (merging +gone == merging without, 3 coords)
;   64  the test can DETECT divergence            (a tampered delta does NOT converge — not vacuously true)
(do
    (let A (list 2 (list 3 -2 5)))
    (let B (list 1 (list 1 4 -5)))
    (let C (list 3 (list 2 -1 -4)))
    (let gone (list 0 (list 9 9 9)))
    (let abc (list A B C))
    ; a tampered third cell (coord2 delta flipped +9) — a DIFFERENT multiset, must NOT converge with abc.
    (let Cx  (list 3 (list 2 -1 9)))
    (let abcx (list A B Cx))
    (let c0 (if (eq (mm-num abc 0) 13) 1 0))
    (let c1 (if (eq (mm-den abc 0) 6) 2 0))
    (let c2 (if (mm-converged-3d? abc (list C B A)) 4 0))
    (let c3 (if (mm-order-stable? A B C) 8 0))
    (let c4 (if (eq (mm-num abc 2) -17) 16 0))
    (let c5 (if (mm-gone-stable? A B C gone) 32 0))
    (let c6 (if (mm-converged-3d? abc abcx) 0 64))
    (add c0 (add c1 (add c2 (add c3 (add c4 (add c5 c6)))))))
